## Infrastructure Configuration

### DigitalOcean Infrastructure
- Droplet: Ubuntu 24.10 (IP: 137.184.15.8)
- Process Manager: PM2 with auto-restart
- Web Server: Nginx v1.24
- Node.js: v18.20.7
- Package Manager: pnpm v9.15.1
- Domain configuration: omniposting.com and api.omniposting.com
- Frontend build optimized with standalone output
- Backend configured with health monitoring
- Image optimization enabled with remote patterns

### Neon.tech Database
- Database configuration managed through environment variables
- Connection pooling enabled for optimal performance
- Separate databases for development, testing, and production
- Test database configured with proper migrations
- Shadow database setup for Prisma migrations

### Environment Variables Required

Frontend (omniposting.com):
```
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.omniposting.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://omniposting.com
```

Backend (api.omniposting.com):
```
DATABASE_URL=[neon-connection-string]
JWT_SECRET=[secure-secret]
```

Note: Environment variables will be configured in Railway.app during deployment setup. Previous Vercel configuration has been removed as part of the migration to Railway.app.

